The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | International cap for girls 
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      International cap for girls 
										      CHIT CHAT                                    Students being counselled at the Global Education Interact      
	La Martiniere for Girls bagged the International School Award from British Council last month. As part of a British Council programme, the school had conducted several activities, workshops, exchange programmes and interactions for a year with participants of other countries.         
	 The project aimed at fostering global citizenship through schools and instilling the values of tolerance, trust and inter-cultural understanding. The participants included nursery, primary as well as secondary students.        
	As part of the project, students got a chance to make friends across the globe. Many activities and workshops were undertaken to make boring topics from the curriculum interesting.        
	Study abroad        
	The sixth edition of education fair  Global Education Interact  was held at a city hotel on June 1. An interactive programme organised by an overseas education consultancy, The Chopras, the event aimed at helping students find out more about foreign universities and the myriad courses offered there.        
	The participants included 47 universities across nine countries. The University of Glasgow, University of Liverpool, University of Nottingham, University of Bristol, Singapore Institute of Management, Middlesex University and the University of Melbourne were some of them.         
	The event was attended by 700 students from city schools and colleges.                                                                                                                                                   
